text: So the Cornell came back to me and one of the professors, he'd done it for eight years. He was looking to expand his portfolio within academics, et cetera. And he said, can you come back and help teach us? So I go back and it's a quant basically model that they do fundamental analysis on top of. So there's a quant research platform up there that we've built, which is really interesting. So Cornell, through their academics and their PhD research, has access to a lot of the data we have here. In fact, there's some data that we don't have here that they've got access to. And that's ones where we have obviously data they don't have. So there's this little bit of expansion on that platform for the data. And the tools are all very straightforward. If you know how to put it all together, it's most of it open source, et cetera. Then it comes to the team where it's able to find students. An undergraduate group, one of the students there called Sparkstone that he put together, I became an advisor on. And they have like this cadre of like eight to ten undergrads who do nothing but work through that platform. And they have their own version of that platform they've taken off on their own. But they basically do research. And I tap into that and try to help them out every once in a while. But that's also led to us having hiring from them. And interns that come from them. So it's this part about pipeline of talent, understanding what's coming through in academics. It's also been a huge part for us on accelerating our ability to adopt the machine learning tools and bring them into our research toolkit. It's just having access where they're getting classes and all the parts with it. So the way I look at that is it's this great. It also, by the way, helps me because I get out. I learn a ton, too, where I don't want to be institutionalized in OSAM either. So it's a part about having where I get to learn. If you want to learn something, there's nothing better than going and standing in front of a classroom and teaching it. I will tell you that. You have to know it. And so it's been just a great experience. And it's one where it continues to add to what I know and my ability to explore the stock market.
